22/11/2004
WASHINGTON, United States -- Croatian European Integration Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic met on Saturday (20 November) with Massachusetts University professor Anamarija Frankic to discuss environmental protection projects. They talked in particular about the COAST project, which envisions the protection of ecosystems in local communities along the Croatian coast, and about a project aimed at protecting the Neretva River delta. The European Commisssion has said the environmental chapter is the only one in which Croatia would require significant resources and technical assistance. (HINA, HRT - 21/11/04)
